<p>It was conceived to assist the work of the Perseus Project, and any others, who want to build treebank databases with teams of non-experts. (The <a href="http://www.coli.uni-saarland.de/projects/sfb378/negra-corpus/annotate.html">@nnotate</a> editor developed at the Universit√§t des Saarlands is a mature project that would be ideal for experienced editors.)</p>
<p><i>Querci</i> provides:
<ul>
  <li>A graphical view of the tree model</li>
  <li>An easy and intuitive drag-and-drop interface for editing</li>
  <li>Input and output conforming to the Perseus Project's treebank XML schema</li>
  <li>A multi-user environment</li>
  <li>Open-source licensing</li>
</ul>
</p>
<h3>Motivation</h3>
<p>Student-created treebanks offer promising opportunities for undergraduate student research and learning, but encoding them with computer markup languages like XML is laborious and probably distasteful to many students. An
easier-to-use editor should increase the number of researchers working on treebanks, and improve the speed and
accuracy of their work. 
</p>
