<h3>Try It</h3>
<p>To get started:
<ol>
<li>Either create your <a href="users/new">own account</a> or <a href="session/new">login</a> as the default, 'guest' (password: 'guest').</li>
<li>You will be directed to a collection of texts and sentences. Select one.</li>
<li>Sentences are modeled one at a time. To indicate a relation between two words in the sentence, use the drop-down menu to select the relation, then drag a word and drop it on the other word with which it has that relationship. For instance. in the sentence <code>Gaius amat Iuliam</code>, You would select 'SUBJ', and drag <code>amat</code> onto <code>Gaius</code>. You would then select 'OBJ' and again drag <code>amat</code> onto <code>Iuliam</code>.
<br/>
Notice that for the purposes of treebank building, many sentence elements are treated as words that would not normally be seen as such. Commas and enclitic <code>que</code>
